CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 12, 1959, pg. A2 reads: "Summer Vacation Is Over for 370,000 Pupils - First Day - Counting parochial schools, 370,000 pupils were back in school Tuesday... right, Cresson, Wayne Miller and cousins, Lyle and Stephanie Wood, with the latter's mother Vivian... - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Wayne Miller with cousins Lyle and Stephanie Wood, and Vivian Wood, standing on stairs of Cresson Elementary School
